
[1]paradox

   PAR'ADOX, n. [Gr. beyond, and opinion; to or suppose.]

   A tenet or proposition contrary to received opinion, or seemingly
   absurd,yet true in fact.

   A gloss there is to color that paradox, and make it appear in show not
   to be altogether unreasonable.
